fields.description: Windows Operating System is available in different editions, which have a specific set of features available. This enum type defines the corresponding edition.
fields.name: EditionType

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: Indicates the Date until which this Operating System edition type is officially supported. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in Pacific Time Zone (PT). For example, 2014-01-01 would mean '2014-01-01T07:00:00Z' in UTC time. Returned by default. Read-only.
fields.name: SupportEndDate
